<ArticleLayout title="About Us | Wavey Dynamics" heading="ABOUT US" subheading="Wavey Dynamics." image="/images/pages/about-hero.jpg" description="Wavey Dynamics delivers motorsport engineering expertise — from McLaren hypercar design to GT3 track support — using a tyre-centric approach to performance.">

  <p class="mb-5 leading-relaxed">Innovation is realised by constantly reaching forward.</p>

  <p class="mb-5 leading-relaxed">Wavey Dynamics' mission is to work with organisations to achieve the absolute maximum of performance from an engineering application. Whether that be for a high-performance road car or a motorsport team on a mission to win a hard-fought championship.</p>

  <p class="mb-5 leading-relaxed">As a form of competitive engineering, motorsport is a particularly useful tool for driving innovation and technology. Drawing from a wide range of scientific disciplines in a manner not quite matched by other engineering branches, motorsport is a powerful platform for developing and applying engineering principles relevant to technology-driven global industries.</p>

  <p class="mb-5 leading-relaxed">With today's engineering complexity, having a comprehensive understanding of fundamental principles has never been more important in order to meet ever-advancing performance benchmarks; the benefit of inspired thought, experience and passion in your corner is instrumental.</p>

  <p class="mb-10 leading-relaxed">Specialising in vehicle dynamics and aerodynamics using a tyre-centric approach, we help to drive a direct link between a deep understanding of technology and clear performance outcomes.</p>

  <p class="mb-5 leading-relaxed">Wavey Dynamics has recently undertaken projects focused on:</p>

  <ul class="wd-list mb-10 space-y-2 leading-relaxed list-none">
    <li>Concept design &amp; body design development for next-generation Hypercar &amp; Supercar projects for a well-known British OEM.</li>
    <li>Concept design of a rising-rate inboard suspension system including pushrod, bell-cranks and damper specification starting from first principles.</li>
    <li>Kinematics design and development (MacPherson &amp; Double Wishbone).</li>
    <li>Track support &amp; data engineering for Mercedes GT3 &amp; GT4 platforms and subsequent setup optimisation.</li>
    <li>CFD development of various aerodynamic devices (body &amp; underbody) in a motorsport context.</li>
    <li>Creation &amp; development of MATLAB-based vehicle dynamics models.</li>
    <li>Implementation of mathematical tyre models to predict thermal and wear effects in real time, including research into tyre physics and tyre strategy.</li>
    <li>Development of a vehicle dynamics fundamentals course for industry and academic students.</li>
  </ul>

  <p class="mb-5 leading-relaxed">Whether in motorsport, or road car technology, our clients are under pressure to continually innovate and require specialist knowledge to operate at the intensity demanded by their competition.</p>

  <p class="mb-5 leading-relaxed">Insight provided by instrumentation, data and analysis techniques and simulation tools complements the implementation of advanced principles. Yet without an in-depth understanding on the physics behind what is happening, it's easy to get lost when things don't perform as expected.</p>

  <p class="mb-10 leading-relaxed">With competence in specialist vehicle performance constantly evolving, are you confident that your understanding is progressing at the same rate?</p>

